    "# Flight Price Prediction Project"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a39d9013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Problem Statement"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5898803",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Anyone who has booked a flight ticket knows how unexpectedly the prices vary. The cheapest available ticket on a given flight gets more and less expensive over time. This usually happens as an attempt to maximize revenue based on - \n",
    "1. Time of purchase patterns (making sure last-minute purchases are expensive) \n",
    "2. Keeping the flight as full as they want it (raising prices on a flight which is filling up in order to reduce sales and hold back inventory for those expensive last-minute expensive purchases) \n",
    "\n",
    "So, you have to work on a project where you collect data of flight fares with other features and work to make a model to predict fares of flights."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,

   "source": [
    "Since Price is my target and it seems to be a continuous feature so this particular problem is a **Regression Problem**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d257558f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Features Information :\n",
    "**Airline**: The name of the airline.  \n",
    "**Journey_date**: The date of the journey  \n",
    "**From**: The source from which the service begins.  \n",
    "**To**: The destination where the service ends.  \n",
    "**Route**: The route taken by the flight to reach the destination.  \n",
    "**D_Time**: The time when the journey starts from the source.  \n",
    "**A_Time**: Time of arrival at the destination.  \n",
    "**Stops**: Total stops between the source and destination.  \n",
    "**Price**: The price of the ticket."
   ]
  },
  {

    "# Feature Extraction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "bb85583d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Converting object data type to datetime in Journey_date column \n",
    "df_fp['Journey_date'] =  pd.to_datetime(df_fp['Journey_date'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "id": "ec5cdec9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extracting Journey year,month and day from Journey_date\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extracting year\n",
    "df_fp[\"Journey_year\"]=pd.to_datetime(df_fp.Journey_date, format=\"%Y/%m/%d\").dt.year\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extracting month\n",

    "# Regression Model Building"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "id": "63b7919e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = df_fp.drop(\"Price\",axis=1)\n",
    "y = df_fp[\"Price\"]"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor\n",
    "vif = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "vif[\"VIF values\"] = [variance_inflation_factor(x.values,i) for i in range(len(x.columns))]\n",
    "vif[\"Features\"] = x.columns\n",
    "vif"
   ]

    "There is no multicolinearity issue in this dataset."

    "# Best Random State"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 63,
   "id": "6b1bcfb9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn import neighbors\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "id": "59cb5361",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Best R2 Score is : 0.6813181031806808  on Random State : 116\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "maxAccu=0\n",
    "maxRS=0\n",
    "for i in range(200):\n",
    "    x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.30, random_state = i)\n",
    "    KNN=neighbors.KNeighborsRegressor()\n",
    "    KNN.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "    pred_rs=KNN.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    r2=r2_score(y_test,pred_rs)\n",
    "    if r2>maxAccu:\n",
    "        maxAccu=r2\n",
    "        maxRS=i\n",
    "print(\"Best R2 Score is :\",maxAccu,\" on Random State :\",maxRS)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "id": "e0e6bd0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=.30,random_state=maxRS)"
   ]

    "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error,mean_absolute_error"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "id": "059690ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "R2_Score:  0.1897812736568698\n",
      "Mean absolute error:  2101.264726904694\n",
      "Mean squared error:  10953837.20037541\n",
      "Root Mean squared error:  3309.65816971714\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "lr=LinearRegression()\n",
    "lr.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "lr.score(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "pred_lr=lr.predict(x_test)\n",
    "print('R2_Score: ',r2_score(y_test,pred_lr))\n",
    "print('Mean absolute error: ',mean_absolute_error(y_test,pred_lr))\n",
    "print('Mean squared error: ',mean_squared_error(y_test,pred_lr))\n",
    "print('Root Mean squared error: ',np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,pred_lr)))"
   ]

    "# KNearest Neighbors Regressor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "id": "58b8a189",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "R2_Score:  0.6813181031806808\n",
      "Mean absolute error:  1356.6927456382002\n",
      "Mean squared error:  4308453.387915519\n",
      "Root Mean squared error:  2075.68142736681\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn import neighbors\n",
    "\n",
    "knn = neighbors.KNeighborsRegressor()\n",
    "knn.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "knn.score(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "pred_knn=knn.predict(x_test)\n",
    "print('R2_Score: ',r2_score(y_test,pred_knn))\n",
    "print('Mean absolute error: ',mean_absolute_error(y_test,pred_knn))\n",
    "print('Mean squared error: ',mean_squared_error(y_test,pred_knn))\n",
    "print('Root Mean squared error: ',np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,pred_knn)))"
   ]

    "# SVR"
   ]
  },

    "# Hyper Parameter Tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5cc46763",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the R2 Score is the Highest and the RMSE score is the lowest in Random Forest Regressor Model, we shall consider it for hyper parameter tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "We shall use GridSearchCV for Hyper Parameter Tuning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 79,
   "id": "1adae065",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 80,
   "id": "bddcaac6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "parameters={\n",
    "    'criterion': ['squared_error','absolute_error'],\n",
    "    'max_depth': [10,20,30],\n",
    "    'max_features': ['sqrt','log2'],\n",
    "    'n_estimators': [100,200,300]}\n",
    "grid_rfr = GridSearchCV(rfr, param_grid = parameters, cv = 5)"
   ]
  },
